    <note>Chen(1) Jiansu [7102] His great great grandfather served the Later Tang as an official in Jiangdong and subsequently became Mingzhou, Yinxian magistrate where he died in the service of the Wuyue kings. With the unification by Song, his grandfather moved to Kaifeng and his father was buried in Henan. He was the husband of Yue(1) Huangmu's [2114] niece. Wang(2) Yi(3)'s [7082] tongnianyou. Wang(2) Anshi's [1762] elder and younger brothers were also tongnianyou with his sons. Cai Xiang. WJ, 38.5b-7a. Wang Anshi, WJ, 99.1024-5 (wife, born Yue(1), who died in 1063 at age 75). Also see documentation for son, Yi [55].</note>
